---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CTASection from '../components/sections/CTASection.astro';
import { seo } from '../lib/seo';

const meta = seo(
  'About',
  'Meridian Dispute Resolution provides structured, neutral mediation across Canada. Based in Saskatchewan. Not legal counsel. Not therapy.',
  '/about'
);
---

<BaseLayout
  title={meta.title}
  description={meta.description}
  canonical={meta.canonical}
>
  <section class="container-narrow">
    <h1>About Meridian</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Meridian Dispute Resolution Inc is a Saskatchewan-based mediation
      consultancy serving individuals, families, and organizations across
      Canada.
    </p>

    <p>
      We provide structured, neutral facilitation for disputes that are too
      consequential to leave unresolved and too complex to resolve informally.
      Our work covers four core areas: workplace and organizational conflict,
      family and separation matters, commercial disputes, and estate and
      inheritance disagreements.
    </p>

    <h2>What We Do</h2>
    <p>
      Mediation is a structured process in which a neutral third party helps
      disputing parties reach a resolution they have shaped themselves. The
      mediator does not decide who is right. They create the conditions for
      productive dialogue, surface the interests beneath stated positions,
      and support parties in identifying options they may not have previously
      considered.
    </p>
    <p>
      The result, when reached, is a negotiated agreement — not an imposed
      outcome. Agreements reached through mediation tend to be more durable
      than those imposed through adjudication because the parties have
      ownership of the result.
    </p>

    <h2>What We Are Not</h2>
    <p>
      Meridian does not provide legal advice or act as legal counsel for any
      party. We are not a therapy service. We do not advocate for any party's
      position. Our role is strictly neutral facilitation — and maintaining
      that neutrality is the foundation of everything we do.
    </p>
    <p>
      Where legal review is advisable — and it often is — we will say so
      directly. Parties are encouraged to retain independent legal counsel
      throughout the process and to have any agreement reviewed before signing.
    </p>

    <h2>Where We Work</h2>
    <p>
      Meridian is based in Saskatchewan and provides mediation services
      virtually across Canada. In-person sessions may be available in
      Saskatchewan depending on the nature of the matter. Our virtual
      process follows the same structured approach as in-person work.
    </p>

    <h2>Our Approach</h2>
    <p>
      We believe that most disputes — workplace, family, commercial, or
      estate — involve people who are capable of reaching a workable
      resolution when the conditions are right. Our job is to create those
      conditions: structure, neutrality, confidentiality, and a process that
      keeps decision-making where it belongs, with the parties themselves.
    </p>
    <p>
      We are not in the business of prolonging engagement or creating
      dependency on the process. The goal of every mediation is resolution —
      arrived at as efficiently and durably as possible.
    </p>
  </section>

  <CTASection
    title="Start with a conversation"
    body="The initial consultation is free. It is also the most straightforward way to find out whether Meridian can help with your situation."
  />
</BaseLayout>
